Variograma emprico

library(geoR)
semiv4 <- variog(gzonaA, max.dist = 15000, uvec = 15)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(semiv4)

library(geoR)
semiv4 <- variog(gzonaA, max.dist = 15000, uvec = 15,
             trend = ~ Thk)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(semiv4)

Estimacin de parmetros

Mxima verosimilitud

library(geoR)
modelo2_lik <- likfit(gzonaA, ini.cov.pars = c(0.8, 6000/sqrt(3)),
                      fix.nugget = TRUE,
                      nugget = 0.02,
                      cov.model = "gaus",
                      #kappa  = 2,
                      #fix.kappa = FALSE,
                      trend = ~ Thk)
## kappa not used for the gaussian correlation function
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## likfit: likelihood maximisation using the function optim.
## likfit: Use control() to pass additional
##          arguments for the maximisation function.
##         For further details see documentation for optim.
## likfit: It is highly advisable to run this function several
##         times with different initial values for the parameters.

Prediccin del modelo

puntos_pred2 <- read.geodata("gzonaApred.csv",
                             header =  TRUE,
                             sep = ";",
                             dec = ",",
                           covar.col = 3)


KC <- krige.control(type = "OK", obj.mod = modelo2_lik,
                    trend.d = trend.spatial("cte", 
                                            geodata = gzonaA,
                                            add = ~ Thk),
                    trend.l = trend.spatial("cte", 
                                            geodata = puntos_pred2,
                                            add = ~ Thk))

sk <- krige.conv(gzonaA, krige = KC, loc = puntos_pred2$coords)
## krige.conv: model with covariates matrix provided by the user
## krige.conv: Kriging performed using global neighbourhood
pred.lim <- range(c(sk$pred))
sd.lim <- range(sqrt(c(sk$kr)))

image(sk, col = gray(seq(0, 1, l = 101)), zlim = pred.lim)
contour(sk, add = T, levels = seq(-0.45, 0.57, 0.1))
points(gzonaA, add = TRUE, cex.max = 2)

image(sk, value = sqrt(sk$krige.var), col = gray(seq(1, 0.3, l = 51)), zlim = sd.lim)
contour(sk, value = sqrt(sk$krige.var), levels = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), add = T)
points(gzonaA$coords, pch = "+")
